<whpage pageid="pgSlideShow" desc="Slide Shows">
<whpagesettings inherit="a">
downLink=pgslide0<!---animationOn-->
</whpagesettings>
(~drShowcaseGlobalHeader~)
WebHub makes it relatively easy to create
slide shows that either auto-advance or require the surfer to
click the [next] button.
<p>
You create a chunk file with the HTML for all the slides (using macros,
etc. as needed).
Then under AppID > Edit Teko Files, you tell WebHub that this particular
file should have animation and sequencing enabled.
(~drShowcaseGlobalFooter~)
</whpage>


<whdroplet name="barSlideShow">
(~GO|pgslide0,animationOn|Auto-advancing~)(~mcHeadingSeparator~)
(~GO|pgslide1,animationOff|Your Pace~)
</whdroplet>

